			<div class="content" id="post-content-1508242">
									

<p>He's not Nobody quite yet, but he will be. In due time.</p>
<p>The nickname Nemo is a double pun. The obvious meaning is that Nemo = No One, and so he'll eventually become Nobody. The far more oblique one goes like this: Nemo is the name of a character in the Pixar movie <em>Finding Nemo</em> &gt; Said character is a fish &gt; Nobody was originally named Foo, or FO0 &gt; Said character of Foo was used as a persona by a former forum member named Fishmonger, known commonly as Fish.</p>
<p>The second pun was unintentional, which makes it even better.</p>

							</div>

								
					
